# End-to-End Business-Grade RAG Implementation for Financial Intelligence Platform

## Problem Statement

The current RAG system in [retrieval.py](file:///c:/Users/Relanto/OneDrive%20-%20Relanto/Desktop/hack/backend/rag/retrieval.py) is a basic prototype with significant gaps:

1. **Mock embeddings** — `USE_MOCK_EMBEDDINGS=true` is hardcoded in [main.py](file:///c:/Users/Relanto/OneDrive%20-%20Relanto/Desktop/hack/backend/main.py#L10), meaning no real semantic search happens
2. **No re-ranking** — Retrieved chunks are used as-is with no relevance scoring refinement
3. **No conversation memory** — Each query is independent; no multi-turn context
4. **Fragile citation extraction** — Heuristic keyword matching produces low-quality citations
5. **No hallucination guardrails** — The system doesn't validate LLM answers against source chunks
6. **Single-collection flat store** — All filings dumped into one "filings" collection with no multi-tenant isolation
7. **No hybrid search** — Only vector similarity; no keyword/BM25 component
8. **No document-scoped queries** — Chatbot doesn't properly scope queries to the active report's documents
9. **No streaming** — Entire response generated before sending to frontend

