## Phase 3 — Context-Aware Prompt Engineering & Conversation Memory

**Goal**: Make the chatbot actually conversational with proper multi-turn memory and financial-domain prompts.

### [NEW] [backend/rag/conversation_memory.py](file:///c:/Users/Relanto/OneDrive%20-%20Relanto/Desktop/hack/backend/rag/conversation_memory.py)
- In-memory conversation store keyed by `report_id` + `session_id`
- Stores last N turns (configurable, default 10)
- Each turn: `{role, content, timestamp, citations_used}`
- **Context compression**: summarize older turns to keep prompt within token limits
- **Coreference resolution helper**: detect pronouns ("it", "they", "the company") and resolve to entities from prior turns

### [NEW] [backend/rag/prompt_templates.py](file:///c:/Users/Relanto/OneDrive%20-%20Relanto/Desktop/hack/backend/rag/prompt_templates.py)
- Structured prompt templates for different query types:
  - `FINANCIAL_RAG_SYSTEM_PROMPT` — main system identity with strict citation rules
  - `FACTUAL_ANSWER_TEMPLATE` — for number/fact queries
  - `ANALYTICAL_ANSWER_TEMPLATE` — for reasoning queries
  - `COMPARATIVE_ANSWER_TEMPLATE` — for cross-company queries
  - `INSUFFICIENT_CONTEXT_TEMPLATE` — when chunks don't contain enough info
- All templates enforce:
  - Inline citations in format `[Company Section - Chunk N]`
  - "I cannot find sufficient evidence" when context lacks answer
  - No speculation beyond retrieved chunks

